name: Up Your Texturing Game - Substance Painter Advanced Techniques
description:
Panel by Fara: The advanced toolsets in Adobe Substance Painter can seem intimidating, but they don't have to be! Fara — a senior environment artist in the games industry — will help take the mystery out of Planar Warp Projection, Blending Modes, Anchor Points, and more. Learn how to improve your workflow by taking advantage of better procedures and techniques within Substance Painter.

http://www.twitter.com/FaraVR

name: Physbones and Beyond, a Guide to Features Obscure
description:
Panel by Happyrobot33: So you can wag your tail with PhysBones and turn your shirt on and off, but what's next? Join me for a showcase of the various lesser-known or never-used methods of creating effects in VRChat for avatars. Things such as PhysBone-based avatar followers, cross-avatar communication using PhysBones, and Quest-compatible effects that VRChat veterans will tell you shouldn't be possible. I'll go over the basics of building such systems and share various tangential ideas for you to build on, alongside resources to get you started.

http://www.twitter.com/MatthewHerber2
http://www.twitch.tv/happyrobot33_

name: Patreon Meetup 3
description: With the help of our supporters on Patreon, we continue pushing the boundaries of what is possible in VR and build our events to be even better! This meetup is a thank you to our Orange tier patrons hosted by members of the Furality Team that bring the magic to life. Link your Patreon account to your profile in order to access this event.

name: VR Content Creator Discussion Panel + Q&A
description:
Panel by PHIA & Thrillseeker: Ever wondered what it's like in the lives of some of the busiest VR content creators on the platform? What does VR look like through the eyes of someone who's been invested in it since the beginning, and what do they think of the future of the industry? Come ask your questions at PHIA and Thrillseekers' Q&A panel. 


https://twitter.com/PHIA_bunny
https://twitter.com/thrilluwu

name: BIPOC Furries Meetup
description: Welcome to the Furality Sylva BIPOC Furies Meeup! What does BIPOC mean? Black, Indigenous, and/or People Of Color! We wanted to make a space for people who want to share their stories, experiences and make connections! Not BIPOC? We still encourage you to come and hear and learn from voices and experiences that you might not have heard before.

name: Cinematic Techniques to Improve Your Video Content
description:
Panel by Astral: Calling all content creators! Astral will show you easy-to-implement techniques that can make your videos more cinematic. Learn about camera angles, character placement, leading room, shot balance, depth of field, and much more.

http://www.twitter.com/astralmelodia
http://www.twitch.tv/astralmelodia

description:
Hosted by Kas: Welcome to the furry take on the popular improv comedy show where everything is made up and the points don't matter! Kas and several of their friends will be engaging in various segments from the show such as 'Scenes From a Hat' and 'Party Quirks'  to create comedy on the fly!

http://www.twitter.com/KasFerret

name: Taming the Virtual Jungle: Furality DevOps Survival Guide
description:
Panel by Furality DevOps Team: Join us to explore and discuss the challenges and opportunities in supporting such a massive virtual convention on VRChat. With over 15,000 attendees at our last convention and a growing team of volunteers all working together remotely, the  DevOps Team has worked throughout the year to advance the technology used at Furality. Whether you are a seasoned DevOps engineer, a technology enthusiast, or simply curious about the behind-the-scenes operations, this panel will have something for you!

https://twitter.com/alofoxx
